# üñ•Ô∏èGuide To Setup The Home Server Project ‚Äì Minecraft with AMP on Ubuntu

This project demonstrates how I set up a self-hosted **Ubuntu-based home server** running a **Minecraft Java Edition server** managed through AMP (Application Management Panel).

---

## üîπ Overview

- **OS:** Ubuntu Server 
- **Access:** SSH & Webmin 
- **Game Panel:** AMP (CubeCoders)
- **Game Hosted:** Minecraft Java & Bedrock Edition
- **Extras:** Expandable to other servers (Valheim, ARK, etc.) via AMP

#Step 1: Update & Upgrade Ubuntu

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

#Step 2: Install OpenSSH

sudo apt install openssh-server -y

-Find server IP:
hostname -I

-Connect from another computer:
ssh <username>@<server-ip>

#Step 3: Install Webmin

wget -qO - http://www.webmin.com/jcameron-key.asc | sudo apt-key add -
sudo add-apt-repository "deb http://download.webmin.com/download/repository sarge contrib"
sudo apt update
sudo apt install webmin -y

-Access in browser:
https://<server-ip>:10000

#Step 4: Install AMP

bash <(wget -qO- https://getamp.sh)

-During setup:
Install Java ‚Üí Y
Install SteamCMD ‚Üí Y
HTTPS ‚Üí N (unless using a domain)
Set admin username & password

-Access AMP:
http://<server-ip>:8080

#Step 5: Activate AMP & Configure

Enter your AMP license
Select Standalone mode
Login with admin credentials

#Step 6: Create Minecraft Server in AMP

1. AMP Dashboard ‚Üí Create Instance
2. Select Minecraft Java Edition
3. Name your server
4. Allocate memory (e.g., 4096 MB)
5. Choose type: Vanilla, Paper, or Fabric
6. Pick Minecraft version
7. Disable Sleep Mode (keep server online)
8. Start server ‚Üí Accept EULA

#Step 7:Connect to Your Server

-In Minecraft:
Multiplayer ‚Üí Direct Connect
Enter: <server-ip>:25565
